news.title: Haryana CM announces regularisation of 210 unauthorised colonies
news.para: The move is aimed at ensuring the provision of essential urban development and amenities for residents residing in these colonies as basic amenities such as roads, sewerage, water supply, and streetlights will be provided to them, Khattar said.

news.title: Country Garden sells stake in Dalian Wanda unit for $428 million
news.para: The sale of its 1.79% holding in shopping mall operator Zhuhai Wanda Commercial Management to Dalian Wanda Commercial Management Group helped shares in Country Garden climb 3% in Thursday trade.

news.title: State capital region to be notified soon in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: A total of 12 objections were submitted by various stakeholders by November 30 to the housing department for perusal which have been disposed of after the public hearing.

news.title: China's Beijing, Shanghai loosen home buying restrictions to aid housing market
news.para: The world's second-biggest economy has struggled to get back on its feet this year after reopening from COVID curbs, largely because its massive property sector has stumbled from one crisis to another in a major blow to consumer and investor confidence.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body drive to cut water supply of societies put on hold
news.para: Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation had issued warnings to 41 societies over non-functional sewage treatment plants (STPs) and warned of action from December 11.

news.title: Shree Cement commissions 11,500 tons per day capacity kiln in its Rajasthan plant
news.para: Established with an investment of approximately Rs 3,500 crore, the plant has a capacity to produce 3.5 million tonnes of cement per annum. Shree Cement has invested on a 33 MW waste heat recovery-based power plant.

news.title: Sewa Grih Rin secures Rs 120 crore debt financing from British International Investment
news.para: The funding will be used to enable the company to enhance its loan book and expand operations into new locations. Axis Bank has facilitated this deal between British International Investment (BII) and Sewa Grih Rin (Sitara).

news.title: Gurugram: Notices & sealing no deterrent, illegal guesthouses still thrive under government nose
news.para: The enforcement wing of department of town and country planning (DTCP) has conducted surveys, served notices and sealed guesthouses running in violation of the norms, but they continue to operate by either removing the seals illegally or obtaining a stay from court, officials said.

news.title: Chennai development body makes and unmakes masterplans
news.para: While the Town and Country Planning Act allows modification of the master plan, it cannot be done for individual survey numbers.  Experts also blame the CMDA for shrinking water bodies through Eri schemes that led to massive 2015 floods.

news.title: Kolkata: Eighteen fake owners, buyers in net for loan fraud
news.para: The case, wrote a senior officer on the KP Facebook page, came to light after the genuine owner of one of the flats lodged a complaint against some persons and the office of a nationalised bank, stating he had been cheated of his property.

news.title: Karnataka: 90,000 tonnes of imported Malaysian sand lying waste
news.para: Industries minister MB Patil told the legislative council on Tuesday that Karnataka had imported a tad over one lakh tonnes of sand to overcome a severe shortage in 2018-19, but it could dispose of only 14,000 tonnes.

news.title: No proposal to increase PMAY-Gramin unit assistance: Union minister
news.para: Furnishing a written reply to the queries posed by Villupuram MP D Ravikumar, Jyoti said the unit assistance provided to the beneficiaries under the PMAY-G scheme is as per the approval of the Union cabinet and at present, there is 'no proposal under consideration in the ministry for increasing the unit assistance'.

news.title: Accommodation with amenities is in the nature of hostel facilities, GST at 12% applies: AAR
news.para: On the same lines, as adopted earlier by the GST-AAR in other instances, notably, in the case of Bengaluru based Srisai Luxurious Stay and Noida based VS Institute and Hostel, the AAR held the provision of accommodation and services to be akin to that of a hostel or guest house which is subject to GST at 12%.

news.title: Mumbai-based builder booked for cheating flat buyer of Rs 3.3 crore
news.para: ​​The Amboli police on Tuesday booked the directors of Saisagar consultant Jayesh, his wife Shradda, his brother Deep Tanna and son Vivek Tanna for cheating and forgery.

news.title: NCLT Mumbai approves sale of Reliance Communications real estate assets
news.para: Resolution professional can sell assets of the company after submission of the resolution plan for approval by the tribunal, according to the order.

news.title: Two promoter entities offload 4.1% stake in Sunteck Realty for Rs 288 crore
news.para: According to the bulk deal data available with the BSE, Satguru Infocorp Services and Starlight Systems disposed of 30 lakh shares each, amounting to a 4.10 per cent stake in Sunteck Realty.

news.title: China pledges fresh support for property market
news.para: Beijing's top decision-makers, including President Xi Jinping, pledged at an annual closed-door meeting held Monday and Tuesday to "actively yet safely defuse risks in the real estate sector" and "meet the reasonable financing needs of real estate enterprises".

news.title: Country Garden has remitted funds to repay yuan bond in full
news.para: Bondholders of a total of 8 million notes, each with a principal of 100 yuan chose to exercise the put option by Nov. 28, while Country Garden has wired funds that fully repaid the principal and interest, the filing showed.
